                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050109-14-victim164 t18050109-14-viclabel65"></join> about the hour of two, in the night of the <rs id="t18050109-14-cd66" type="crimeDate">5th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050109-14-off64 t18050109-14-cd66"></join>, and burglariously stealing a miniature picture set in gold, value 3 l. a compass, value 1 l. a leather bag, value 1 d. a canvass bag, value 1 d. twenty guineas, eleven half-guineas, sixteen seven-shilling-pieces, three crowns, four half-crowns, sixty shillings, nine sixpences, a piece of foreign silver coin called a French crown, value 4 s. 6 d. a French half-crown, value 2 s. 3 d. two other pieces of foreign coin, value 1 s. a Bill of Exchange, value 3007 l. 8 s. 11 d. a Bill of Exchange, value 500 l. a Bill of Exchange, value 434 l. 14 s. a Bill of Exchange, value 500 l. a Bill of Exchange, value 100 l. a Bill of Exchange, value 25 l. a Bill of Exchange, value 360 l. three Bank of England notes, value 5 l. each, two other Bank of England notes, value 2 l. each, twenty Bank of England notes, value 20 l. the said Bills of Exchange, Bank of England notes, and monies, at the time of committing the burglary, being the property of the said 
                     <persName id="t18050109-14-person165">
                        Robert 
                        Shawe
                     <interp inst="t18050109-14-person165" type="surname" value="Shawe"></interp>
